# KeeNet build-time configuration.
# Copy to `.env` (or `.env.local`) and fill in. All values are OPTIONAL — with
# none set, the build uses a relative base and ships no cloud credentials
# (users can still paste their own client IDs in Settings → Storage).
#
# Vite only exposes VITE_-prefixed vars to the build. Anything set here is
# baked into the client bundle and therefore PUBLIC. All OAuth providers run
# as PKCE public clients: there is no client_secret support — never put a
# real secret in any VITE_ variable.

# ---- Public base path -------------------------------------------------------
# Where the app is served. Default './' (relative) works at any mount point,
# e.g. behind Caddy at /keenet. Set an absolute path/URL only if you need one.
# VITE_BASE_URL=/keenet/

# ---- OAuth client ids (public, PKCE) -----------------------------------------
# Register your own apps per provider and set the redirect URIs below.
# VITE_DROPBOX_CLIENT_ID=
# VITE_GDRIVE_CLIENT_ID=
# VITE_ONEDRIVE_CLIENT_ID=

# ---- OAuth redirect URIs ----------------------------------------------------
# The WEB redirect URI is derived at runtime from the page URL (origin+path),
# so register e.g. https://your.domain/keenet/ on each provider.
# These override the packaged desktop/mobile redirect URIs (register them too):
# VITE_OAUTH_DESKTOP_REDIRECT_URI=https://localhost/keenet-oauth
# VITE_OAUTH_MOBILE_REDIRECT_URI=keenet://oauth2redirect
